{
  "texts": [
    "The maximum difference in D eff appears at δ = 0.3 for r = 1:5 (Fig. 9g).",
    "CW particles diffuse faster in the CCW lattice (δ ∈ [0.5, 1)) than in the mirrored CW lattice, namely, a CW lattice with the same value of |δ -0.5|.",
    "Likewise, CCW particles diffuse faster in the CW lattice.",
    "Interestingly, these findings are similar to an existing simulation work 83, which found that \"levogyre\" (CCW) CAPs are trapped in a \"left-chiral\" flower of ellipse obstacles but can freely enter and leave a \"right-chiral\" flower, whereas \"dextrogyre\" (CW) CAPs are trapped in a \"right-chiral\" flower but can freely enter and leave a \"left-chiral\" flower.",
    "The two works are different for the following reasons: (1) The obstacle particle in ref."
  ]
